Market Definition

Medical alert systems are devices designed to provide immediate assistance in emergencies, particularly for individuals with medical conditions or seniors living alone. Typically worn as a pendant or bracelet, they allow users to summon help with the press of a button, connecting them to a monitoring center staffed by trained professionals who can dispatch emergency services or contact designated caregivers. These systems offer peace of mind to users and their families, ensuring prompt response during medical crises, falls, or other emergencies.

